However, I assume we will be more prepared for Doomshade and will likely have at least ONE mage drop a ton of Mod Rods to be used in the fight.  As long as I have my Mana Shield up before the fight (absorbs 591 dmg) and have a healer available and/or regeneration buff, the wizards can Mana Burn the mob early on (since Mana Burn is like zero aggro), and then Mod Rod/Mana Robe (which I have) up to full mana, and continue as normal.  If anything, the period of time after the Mana Burn to Mod Rod to full mana provides the tanks more time to aquire aggro, and allows us to nuke on a more full burn once we regain our mana so we waste less mana on spells like concussion (aggro reduction spell) throughout the battle.  In the battle where I did 32k dmg I cast concussion twice after almost EVERY nuke.  Concussion only costs 25 mana to cast, but in a fight wherein I do 32k dmg, that easilly adds up to 1350 mana wasted on Concussion alone.<br>
<br>
As long as we prepare well and have mod rods available, Koadic's or C2, maybe a bard for Bardsong, etc...  Using Mana Burn is Highly efficient.  According to the statistics I obtain parsing my logs I average a critical hit 11% of the time.  If I Critical Strike a Mana Burn that can easilly chew away 12-16k damage off the mob with almost NO AGGRO immediately.  In the time it takes me to regain full mana with Mod rods, etc (roughly 30 seconds) I would likely only cast enough normal nukes to do 2-3k.  To me, this is enough extra damage to justify the mod rod preparation, if possible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ustoneglacier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stoneglacier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#70DB93>(5/17/02 1:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Doomshade</span><hr size=1> /em is impressed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
